we have a starting five define arterisk or dot on the left, then commands and what you choose to do on the right.

* * * * *  command

# Field-by-field explanation

Field   	    Position    	    Values  	                What it means
Minute  	      1st *	            0–59	                    Which minute of the hour to run the command
Hour    	      2nd *	            0–23	                    Which hour of the day to run the command
Day of Month	  3rd *	            1–31	                    Which day of the month to run the command
Month	          4th *	            1–12	                    Which month to run the command
Day of Week	      5th *	            0–7 (0 or 7 = Sunday)	    Which day of the week to run the command


# NOTE
In shell scripting, * represents “match zero or more characters” in filenames or strings.
It’s a shorthand way to select multiple files or patterns without typing them all individually.

# EXAMPLE

* * * * * echo "Hello world" >> /tmp/test.log
Runs every minute.
Appends "Hello world" to /tmp/test.log each time.
After an hour, the file will have 60 new lines.

# Special Characters when working with cron Jobs


Symbol     Meaning 
 `*`      every value 
 `,`      multiple values 
 `-`      range 
 `/`      step value 

 # EXAMPLE

```bash
 */5 * * * *    echo "we are live from the shell"  > /tmp/start.txt
 ```
This command above runs every **5 minutes**.


